+## Appendix A — Methodology, Environment, Screenshots
+
+### Environment
+
+- Repo at `/home/runner/work/dataslope/dataslope`, branch the agent was launched on.
+- `npm install` + `npm run dev` (Next.js 16.2.6 + Turbopack) — server live at `http://localhost:3000`.
+- Playwright Chromium 1223 headless, viewport 1600×1000.
+- Sandbox network policy blocked `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net` (used for the SQLite-WASM and DuckDB-WASM ESM modules) and `https://fonts.googleapis.com`. PGlite (Postgres) is bundled locally and loaded successfully, which is why most of the live walkthrough findings are from `/playground/postgres`.
+
+### What was tested live (Postgres)
+
+- Cold load of the playground; observed banner, sidebar, sample-DB picker, and the in-app workspace pill.
+- Opened **Add Table** dialog; tried the type combobox both by clicking the chevron and by typing.
+- Pressed **Escape** to verify it would close the modal — it did not.
+- Clicked **Cancel** to return to the playground.
+
+### What was audited via source
+
+- SQLite playground (`app/_components/sql/SqlPlayground.tsx`, shared `components/*`) — engine WASM failed to load, but the UI is the same shell used by Postgres so most observations transfer; engine-specific gaps were cross-referenced against the runtime in `app/_components/runtime/sqlite*.ts`.
+- DuckDB playground (`app/_components/duckdb/DuckDbPlayground.tsx`) — engine WASM failed to load; static audit covered the Create Table dialog, the schema/file sidebar, the unique pedagogical pre-populated tabs, and `app/_components/runtime/duckdb.ts` for `dropEntity`, `cleanDuckDbSchema`, `updateRows`.
+- All workflow-specific findings include `file:line` citations so they can be re-verified locally.
